article.headline: Nebraska 82, Alabama A&M 55
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Freshman Ryan Anderson scored 13 points in the first half to help Nebraska build an early 10-point lead, and the Cornhuskers rolled to a 82-55 win over Alabama A&M on Sunday. Nebraska (6-2) played without its leading scorer, Aleks Maric, but two freshmen stepped up to lead the team. Anderson scored 19 points to lead Nebraska, and fellow freshman Sek Henry added 11. Alabama A&M (5-4) fell behind 18-8 when Nebraska's Charles Richardson made a pair of free throws with 12:01 left in the first half. The Bulldogs never got closer than eight the rest of the game. Nebraska held the Bulldogs without a field goal in the last 6 minutes, 55 seconds of the first half as part of a 20-4 run. Alabama A&M's four points during the run came on free throws. Nebraska led 44-20 at the half. The Bulldogs were able to cut the Nebraska lead to 19 midway through the second half. But Nebraska went up by as many as 30 while playing a lineup of reserves through most of the second half. Jamel White and Paul Velander added 10 each for the Huskers. Trant Simpson led Alabama A&M with 16 points. Evan Hilton had 12 for the Bulldogs.
